---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Custom Saw Blades | Engineered for Your Application"
  description="Custom engineered saw blades designed for your specific material and machine requirements. Premium carbide grades, precision tooth geometry, application optimization."
>
  <section class="gradient-hero text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6">Custom Saw Blades</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
          Engineered-to-order blades optimized for your specific material and cutting requirements.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-custom">
        <h2>When Standard Blades Fall Short</h2>
        <p>
          Standard off-the-shelf blades are often the weakest link in high-volume industrial cutting operations. 
          Materials with unique properties—high-silica hardwoods, abrasive composites, hardened steels—destroy 
          general-purpose blades prematurely.
        </p>

        <h3>The Material Science of Custom Carbide</h3>
        <p>
          Our custom blades utilize premium sub-micron grade carbides, optimized for specific wear patterns. 
          By matching the binder chemistry to your workpiece, we significantly extend sharpening intervals.
        </p>

        <h4>Carbide Grades Available</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>C-2 Grade:</strong> 6-10% cobalt for general-purpose with balance of hardness and toughness</li>
          <li><strong>C-3 Grade:</strong> 4-6% cobalt for abrasive materials like particleboard and MDF</li>
          <li><strong>C-4 Grade:</strong> 2-4% cobalt for non-ferrous metals and high-silica content woods</li>
          <li><strong>Micro-Grain:</strong> Sub-micron grain structure for maximum edge retention</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Engineering Precision Tooth Geometry</h3>
        <p>
          Every custom blade is designed using advanced CAD/CAM software to determine optimal:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rake Angles:</strong> Positive for aggressive cutting, negative for hardened materials</li>
          <li><strong>Clearance Angles:</strong> Prevent rubbing while maintaining tooth strength</li>
          <li><strong>Gullet Volume:</strong> Matched to chip size and evacuation requirements</li>
          <li><strong>Tooth Count:</strong> Balanced for cut quality and feed rate</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Custom Manufacturing Process</h3>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Application Analysis:</strong> Material properties, cutting parameters, machine specifications</li>
          <li><strong>CAD Design:</strong> 3D modeling of tooth geometry and blade body</li>
          <li><strong>Carbide Selection:</strong> Grade optimization for your specific application</li>
          <li><strong>CNC Manufacturing:</strong> Precision grinding with diamond wheels</li>
          <li><strong>Quality Verification:</strong> Measurement and test cutting validation</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Specifications We Customize</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <strong class="text-primary">Diameter:</strong> 4" to 84"+
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <strong class="text-primary">Kerf:</strong> 0.125" to 0.375"+
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <strong class="text-primary">Arbor:</strong> 1" to 2.5"+
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <strong class="text-primary">Tooth Count:</strong> 24 to 120+
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Need a Custom Solution?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        Our application engineers will design the optimal blade for your specific requirements.
      </p>
      <a href="/carbidesaws-rebuild/contact" class="bg-secondary text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary transition">
        Start Custom Design
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
